# ImageBackground Pattern

`ImageBackground` does **not** size itself — it inherits dimensions from its parent or its own `style`. Without explicit sizing it collapses to 0×0 and the image disappears.

## The Two-Layer Pattern (ALWAYS use this)

Wrap `ImageBackground` in an outer `View` that owns the shape/clip, then give `ImageBackground` `width: "100%", height: "100%"` so it fills that container. Content goes **inside** `ImageBackground` as children — the children's natural height drives the outer View's height.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<View className="overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
  <ImageBackground
    source={bgImage}
    resizeMode="cover"
    style={{ width: "100%", height: "100%" }}
  >
    {/* content drives the height */}
    <View className="p-md gap-md">
      {/* ... */}
    </View>
  </ImageBackground>
</View>
```

## Why NOT absolute-positioned `<Image>`

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG — image collapses because parent has no explicit height
<View className="overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
  <Image
    source={bgImage}
    resizeMode="cover"
    className="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full"
  />
  <View className="p-md gap-md">{/* ... */}</View>
</View>
```

`h-full` / `height: "100%"` on an absolutely-positioned child resolves against the parent's **explicit** height. When the parent is content-sized (HUG), it has no explicit height, so `100%` resolves to `0` and the image is invisible.

## Fixed-size containers

When the parent has a fixed height (e.g. a full-screen hero), the absolute approach works — but `ImageBackground` is still preferred for clarity:

```tsx
// ✅ Also fine when parent height is explicit
<View style={{ height: 200 }} className="overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
  <ImageBackground source={bgImage} resizeMode="cover" style={{ flex: 1 }}>
    {/* ... */}
  </ImageBackground>
</View>
```

## Checklist

- [ ] `ImageBackground` always has an explicit `style` with `width`/`height` or `flex: 1`
- [ ] `overflow-hidden` + `borderRadius` live on the **outer** `View`, not on `ImageBackground`
- [ ] Never use `<Image className="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full">` on a content-sized parent
